doc.previous: For a subsonic application of a fixed geometry C D nozzle see section Low ratio nozzle
doc.after: Non afterburning subsonic engines have nozzles of a fixed size because the changes in engine performance with altitude and subsonic flight speeds are acceptable with a fixed nozzle This is not the case at supersonic speeds as described for Concorde in section Nozzle area control during dry operation
